summary:
Throughout my studies and career I’ve always been interested in the use of math in order to solve real-life problems, and how this can have an impact on society. From implementing a stochastic model describing the spread of a sheep disease to developing deployable ML algorithms to detect fraud, I’m eager to make the world a better place. 

I consider myself and advocate for diversity and gender equity, and I’m always up for a constructive discussion about these topics.

In my free time I really enjoy bouldering, a very recent obsession, and reading novels or autobiographies. Moreover, I love to spend my weekend cooking for the neighbourhood and for my family and friends.
